column5: Added functions as attribute values: `onclick: -> alert 'hi'`. Closes #79 (thanks @smathy).
Tweaks to "prefixed attributes" from colinta, part of #78.
Support for nested/grouped attributes. a href:'/login\', data: {icon:'arrow-r', iconpos:'right'}, 'Login' => Login
Hooked in express plugin with express's nice error reporting stuff.
Fixed #71: indexOf not supported in IE7 (thanks @jaekwon).
Fixed #69 (`coffeekup -w` only compiles upon first change).
Added compile to js option to CLI. Closes #58.
set encoding in readFile to get string instead of buffer
Added missing elements from the HTML 5 spec (both valid and obsolete). Closes #66 (thanks @aeosynth).
Added note to run `cake build` before trying examples (prompted by #63).
Correctly relaying stdout and stderr in Cakefile.
Added contributors as output by `git summary` to package.json.
Added more resources and related projects.
Split up resources and related projects.

Whipped this little html2coffeekup project up. It's pretty rough, but it managed to convert 50+ non-trivial html files for me without too much manual cleanup needed. Saved me a lot of time, so it might do the same for someone else.
Renamed the template param back to `data`.
Changed: now accepting all options at the "root" of the input object.
Updated tests to af9cfe (cache off by default).
Set the param of compiled templates to an empty object by default.
In `ck.render`, option `cache` is now `false` by default.
Moved last TODO to github issues.
Correctly handling booleans as attribute values.
Fixed reference error in the 'indent' function.
Added instructions to install edge and mentioned 'reference.md'.
Added divitis example with new id/class shortcut.
Added the express adapter to readme.
Correctly handle numbers and booleans when used as tag contents.
Renamed 0.2.4beta to 0.3.0beta (more changes than initially planned).
Using '.call(this);' instead of '();' in js generated by the 'coffeescript' tag.
Making sure hardcoded functions have access to "data" as "@/this".
Added link to Mark Hahn's intro to CoffeeKup.
Added ice (CoffeeKup and Eco for Rails) to related projects.
Added related projects and thanks sections to readme.
coffeescript -> code() now correctly adds coffeescript helpers to the output.
Doctypes now editable at coffeekup.doctypes. Using doctype 'default' if none provided.

coffeescript src: 'file.coffee' generates <script src="file.coffee" type="text/coffeescript"></script>

Thanks to @henrikh for https://github.com/mauricemach/coffeekup/pull/33
TODO: coffeescript function must include coffeescript_helpers in output.
First go at updating the readme / added annotated source through docco.

First go at 0.2.4.

Refactored functions input to fix issues with newer express versions and
improve integration. Thanks for @aldonline, @luispedro and @JasonGiedymin
for their contributions.

- No need to specify `context`: `foo` in `ck.render tpl, foo: 'bar'` now
available as `h1 @foo`.
- Locals implemented through `with` by default, hardcoded as an option.
- Gone with `ck_*` locals, now all junk inside a `__ck` object.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/aeosynth/coffeekup into aeosynth-master
Converting any ampersands to & when escaping html, instead of /&(?!\w+;/.
Linking to the latest coffee-script.js in examples.
Fixed declaration of tags on CoffeeScript 0.9.5.
Fixed string templates compilation in opera.
Added link to live demo on README.
Custom tags signature fixed, added tests.
Added escaping function and autoescape option.
Templates now compiled to standalone functions.
Added creationix's haml-js to the benchmark.

CLI tool now more like the coffee command:

- Output is written to [file].html by default. Use -p to print to stdout.
- You can use -w to watch source files and compile them whenever they change.
- Also added -f to format HTML output (it's minified by default).
Oops, let's not forget customizable locals.
Fixed nested rendering (shown in Meryl example).

Internal rewrite addressing:

- Preservation of the context (@) you provide for rendering. Previously it
was copied over for each rendering, now it's used by reference.

- Context pollution. All locals had a corresponding reference in the context.
Now it's untouched.
Added framework adapters to ease integration.
Removing options.compile from Vladimir's fork, keeping fixes.
Three delicious flavours added to /examples/browser to illustrate deployment options.

Version bump, enabled "compilerless" client-side usage, fixed bug.

- Doesn't *require* coffeescript on the client side anymore. If the compiler is available great, treat string templates as coffeescript and try to compile them. But if not, assume string templates are given in javascript already and just execute them.

- Improved unwrapping logic and regexes.

- Fixed bug: any value returned by child functions (ex: "ul -> li" => "ul(function(){return li()})") were being added to the buffer. Now adding strings only.
Update to CoffeeScript 0.9.4 (boy, that was fast).

Fixed context vars at the root and issue with the coffeescript "filter".

* Vars provided as "context" (attached to this/@) were not available at the
root of the document.

* Previous version attempted to unwrap js generated by the coffeescript "filter"
from its outer function. But it will always inevitably return the last
statement, since it's just a .toString() of code generated by the cs compiler.
So now, instead of unwrapping the js, we just call its outer function.
Added .md extension to README for github.
